project.name: Overture Maps Foundation
project.description:
The Overture Maps Foundation intends to power current and next-generation map products by creating reliable, easy-to-use, and interoperable open map data. We incorporate map data from multiple sources including Overture members, government organizations, and open data sources including OpenStreetMap, map it to a common schema for ease of consumption, and assign/manage stable identifiers to allow data consumers to more easy connect datasets together. 

Overture Maps Foundation is a Joint Development Foundation Project, an affiliate of the Linux Foundation.
project.license_type: Code is MIT, Schema is CC-By 4.0, Data is mostly CDLA and other CC licenses based on data source.
